Opgave 1

1

Givet:

\[ R(s) = \frac{1}{s} \quad G(s)= \frac{10}{s+10}\\ C(s) = R(s)G(s) \]

Derfor:

\[ C(s) = \frac{10}{s(s+10)} = \frac{1}{s} - \frac{1}{s+10} \] Dermed: \[ c(t) = 1 - e^{-10t} \]

\[ \tau = \frac{1}{10}\]

2

Givet:

\[ R(s) = \frac{1}{s} \quad G(s)= \frac{20}{s+15}\\ C(s) = R(s)G(s) \]

Derfor:

\[ C(s) = \frac{20}{s(s+15)} = \frac{\frac{20}{15}}{s} - \frac{\frac{20}{15}}{s+10} \] Dermed: \[ c(t) = \frac{20}{15} \left(1 - e^{-15t}\right) \]

\[ \tau = \frac{1}{15}\]

Opgave fra Nise pdf

A

Vi har:

\[ G(s) = 400 \cdot \frac{1}{s^2+12s+400} \]

\[ C(s) = \frac{1}{s} \cdot 400 \cdot \frac{1}{s^2+12s+400} = 400 \cdot \frac{1}{s(s^2+12s+400)} \]

Her er polparret:

\[ p =-6 \pm 2\sqrt{91} = -6\pm 19.08 \]

Det giver fÃ¸lgende underdÃ¦mpede step respons

\[ c(t) = A + B e^{-\sigma t} + cos(\omega t - \phi) \] Hvor \[ \sigma = 6 \quad \omega = 19.08 \]

AltsÃ¥:

\[ c(t) = A + B e^{-6 t} + cos(19.08 t - \phi) \]

B

\[ G(s) = \frac{900}{s^2+90*s+900} \]

Denne funktion har polerne:

\[ p_1 = -11.46 \quad p_2 = -78.54\\ \sigma_1 = -11.46 \quad \sigma_2 = -78.54 \]

Dermed er det et overdÃ¦mpet respons:

\[ K_1 \cdot e^{-\sigma_1 t} + K_2 \cdot e^{-\sigma_2 t} \]

Stepresponset bliver:

\[ A + K_1 \cdot e^{-11.46 t} + K_2 \cdot e^{-78.54 t} \]
